data.text:
When William McKinley was born on 3 September 1796, in Kentucky, United States, his father, Michael Green McKinley, was 31 and his mother, Sarah Fouts, was 31. He married Mary Cunningham in August 1819, in Miami, Ohio, United States. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 8 daughters. He died on 26 August 1845, in Johnson Township, Champaign, Ohio, United States, at the age of 48, and was buried in Leatherwood Cemetery, Lena, Brown Township, Miami, Ohio, United States.

1801 Â· Cane Ridge Revival

The Cane Ridge Revival took place for six days in Cane Ridge, Kentucky. From August 6, 1801- August 12 or 13, 1801, around 20 thousand people gathered together for what was called the Second Great Awakening.

1803

Ohio was the first state admitted to the Union from the Northwest Territory.

1810 Â· Change of capital city

Zanesville becomes the new state capital.
